If you ever want to kill the current command, press Ctrl + “6” + Shift
Router


Display all possible choices
“?”


Turn on privileged commands, enter user privileged mode
“enable”


Enter configuration mode, from privileged exec mode 
“Router#configure”


Revert to previous “shell” mode
“exit”


Configure ip interface FastEthernet 1/0, in Privileged Exec Mode
“Router(config)#interface FastEthernet 1/0”


Assign a static ip address to an interface
“Router(config-if)#ip address 192.168.1. 255.255.255.0”


Turn on an interface, disable shutdown
“Router(config-if)#no shutdown”


To configure or make dhcp pool named “pool0”
“Router(config)#ip dhcp pool pool0


To assign a network address range to the pool
“Router(dhcp-config)#network 192.168.1.0 255.255.255.0”


To assign a default router to the pool
“Router(dhcp-config)#default-router 192.168.1.1”


To enable a password
“Router(config)#enable password supersecretpassword“




Switch


Turn on privileged commands, enter user privileged mode
“Enable”


Turn on privileged exec mode
“Switch#config”


To configure the vlan database
“Switch#vlan database”


To add a vlan to the database
“Switch(vlan)#vlan 11”


To name a vlan
“Switch(vlan)#vlan 11 name IA”


To configure an interface 
“Switch(config)#interface FastEthernet 0/1”


To change a port’s interface to a specific VLAN
“Switch(config-if)#switchport access vlan 11”




